Nambivelnadhan, the error is very clear from the message:

> **SQLSTATE[23000]: Column `user_id` cannot be null**

This means **Laravel is trying to insert a post but `user_id` is empty**.

Your controller code:

```php
'user_id' => auth()->id()
```

But **auth()->id() is returning NULL**.

That means **no user is logged in** when creating the post.

---

# 🔍 Why This Happens

Your route probably looks like this:

```php
Route::resource('/admin/posts', PostController::class);
```

But **it is not protected by authentication middleware**.

So Laravel cannot detect the logged-in user.

---

# ✅ Solution 1 (Best Solution)

Protect admin routes using **auth middleware**.

Open:

```
routes/web.php
```

Change to:

```php
use App\Http\Controllers\Admin\PostController;
use App\Http\Controllers\Admin\CategoryController;
use App\Http\Controllers\Admin\DashboardController;

Route::middleware(['auth'])->prefix('admin')->group(function () {

    Route::get('/dashboard',[DashboardController::class,'index']);

    Route::resource('/categories', CategoryController::class);

    Route::resource('/posts', PostController::class);

});
```

Now **only logged-in users can create posts**.

---

