# ✅ Solution 3 (Safer Controller Code)

Update your controller store method:

📄 `PostController.php`

```php
public function store(Request $request)
{
    if(!auth()->check()){
        return redirect('/login');
    }

    Post::create([
        'title'=>$request->title,
        'description'=>$request->description,
        'category_id'=>$request->category_id,
        'user_id'=>auth()->id()
    ]);

    return redirect('/admin/posts')
    ->with('success','Post Added Successfully');
}
```

---

# ✅ Check Your Model Fillable

📄 `Post.php`

```php
protected $fillable = [
    'title',
    'description',
    'category_id',
    'user_id'
];
```

If `user_id` is missing here → Laravel will ignore it.

